        <p class="card-text text-center"><i>Only One Time Zone in China</i> <br>
          China has one official time zone, China Standard Time (CST), which is 8 hours ahead of UTC. In China, the time
          zone is known as Beijing Time.

          In Xinjiang, China's westernmost region, the Uyghur population unofficially uses a different local time known
          as Xinjiang Time or Ürümqi Time, which is 2 hours behind CST.

          China observes China Standard Time all year. There are no Daylight Saving Time clock changes.</p>
